The White House has sent several nominations to the Senate for various positions. These include Adewale Adeyemo, who has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of the Treasury, replacing Marisa Lago. Brian James Egan has been nominated to be the Legal Adviser of the Department of State, replacing Harold Hongju Koh who has resigned. Matthew T. McGuire has been nominated to be the United States Executive Director of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development for a two-year term, replacing Ian Hoddy Solomon whose term has expired. John E. Mendez has been nominated to be a Director of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation, replacing Sharon Y. Bowen who has resigned. Additionally, Mendez has also been nominated for reappointment as a Director of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation.